narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: YES. An essential class for any music major/ serious music student. Training your ear is perhaps the most important aspect of becoming a musician or scholar and this class does that along with some rigorous rhythm training and keyboard work. Becoming a better musician in a relaxed environment --- the perfect class if you put in the time and effort.
This class was great! Fun but I still feel like I learned a lot, and Lalli is a fantastic teacher. Highly recommended.

With hesitation. Lalli is a wonderful man, and the skills you learn here can be truly valuable--drilling rhythms is something that every musician should have to do, and atonal dictation/sightsinging is super important for choristers, at least. However, the class could have been much more focused and covered much more ground than it did.
